This was a phenomenally frustrating game. Game controls leave a lot to be desired, and often times were so unintuitively nonsensical that I had no clue how to proceed. The answers to puzzles make absolutely no reasonable sense, the clues in the diary are so vague they are often useless. I paid for all 3 and uninstalled them before finishing. I was on the last level but got fed up with how difficult the gameplay was. Background was beautiful or this would get 1 star

Finally a fun game that has puzzles and keeps you entertained. The story is great and the music is awesome.

The graphics are stunning & the worlds are rich & so imaginative. Unfortunately the gameplay is often poor, too much trial & error instead of actually solving puzzles & feeling the accomplishment of doing so. The controls are fine & everything ran smoothly, no glitches. As for the story, I could see the ending coming a mile off. It's very smart to have the episodes separate, the first for free & the others fairly low in price. There's no way I would have paid over ¬£5 for this otherwise.
It is captivating in a way. Very interesting concept to keep you going.

The first level with the tree was frustrating to navigate - I barely held interest to complete it. The next level, with the teleportation, is even worse. Boring. Confusing. There isn't enough story or interest for me to attempt dozens and dozens of arbitrary combinations. Even your hint system is boring and confusing. So sorry I spent money on this waste of time and energy.
